message:
Hey guys, here is a message from your local habitat for humanity chapter. Check it out!

Do you have plans for winter break? The UMN Habitat for Humanity Chapter currently has openings in their alternative winter break trips! The dates of the trip are January 8, 2017 - January 14, 2017.

Here is a general overview of what a winter break trip with Habitat for Humanity entails:

work Monday through Friday from approximately 8 a.m. to 4 p.m.
projects may include improving existing housing structures, helping build a house or volunteering on other projects that help meet the goals of Habitat for Humanity in the community
evenings to be free to use as your group desires (visit the beach, explore the town, etc.)
Locations include:

York, Pennsylvania 
Winston-Salem, North Carolina
New Smyrna, Florida
Email toni.marano@uofmhabitat.org  for more information!He
